    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Range Yoke Bolts and Recommended Torque of Auxiliary Drive Gear Nut</title>
        <para>Install the 2 bolts into the range yoke and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m) (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13027i1">right, Figure 181</hotlnk>). Tighten auxiliary drive gear retaining nut to 90 to
            120 ft-lbs. (122 to 163 N&#183; m) (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13027i1">left, Figure 181</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f13027i1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027i1" filename="../figg13/g13027i1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 181. Install Bolts into Range Yoke and Tighten Auxiliary Drive Gear Retaining Nut</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
